main event: A farmer named Lewis Belue observed a bright, elongated UFO near Wakarusa, Indiana on September 7, 1967.
interesting points: The object changed direction multiple times and emitted bursts of speed,The light was bright enough to be seen through cloud cover,The object was reported to have landed in a field, but no physical evidence was found,Law enforcement confirmed it was not a known aircraft, The sighting lasted for about 1 hour from 9:25 P.M. to 10:25 P.M.
sighted object: bright elongated object in the sky
witness description: Lewis Belue, 54, farmer, reported the sighting to state police
